<h2 class="page-title span-24">Case Study: David Suzuki Foundation</h2>

<div class="header span-24">
  <div class="span-19 last">
    <h1><span class="dark-green">The David Suzuki Foundation had a tight deadline. </span><br />Gossamer met it.</h1>
    <img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-suzuki-120x54.png" width="120" height="54" alt="David Suzuki Foundation" />
  </div>
</div><!-- end .header -->

<div class="span-15 append-1 content-text"><!-- main-col -->
  <h2>Challenge</h2>
  <p>
    When the David Suzuki Foundation designed their new website, they had
    difficulty securing a host that could provide the services and performance
    that they required for their new platform, all within a limited budget.
  </p>

  <h2>Solution</h2>
  <p>
    Feeling strongly about supporting the organization's agenda, Gossamer
    started by providing discounted services to the David Suzuki Foundation.
    Part of this solution included dedicated hosting, which eliminated the
    speed issues experienced by the original site. Additionally, Gossamer
    developed a tie-in between their blogging software Moveable Type and Solr,
    an open source search technology. This provided much more relevant results
    in near instant response, and included new functionality (i.e. highlighted
    search terms).
  </p>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <p>
    By consulting with the Foundation, Gossamer was able to make functional
    improvements to various aspects of the site, improving overall user
    experience. Meanwhile, a fully managed, dedicated hosting solution gave the
    organization the reliability and stability it needed in order to ensure
    that visitors could properly access the blog without the long wait times
    they had previously been experiencing.
  </p>

  <p class="more"><a href="/development/">More about our custom development&nbsp;<span>&raquo;</span></a></p>

  <h2>Other Case Studies</h2>
  <p>
    <a href="/results/not-for-profit/icbl.html"><img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-icbl-110x90.png" width="110" height="90" alt="International Campaign to Ban Landmines" /></a>
